dcterms:description: The RESIDE dataset consists of five subsets: Indoor Training Set (ITS), Outdoor Training Set (OTS), Synthetic Object Testing Set (SOTS), Unannotated real Hazy Images (URHI), and real Task-driven Testing Set (RTTS). It is used for benchmarking single-image dehazing and beyond.

dcterms:description: The Rain1400 dataset contains 1400 image pairs with rain streaks of various sizes, shapes, and directions. It is used for training and testing deraining algorithms.

dcterms:description: The GoPro dataset contains 2103 image pairs, with each pair consisting of a sharp image and a blurry image. It is used for training and testing deblurring algorithms.

dcterms:description: The RealBlur-J dataset includes real-world blurry images for learning and benchmarking deblurring algorithms. It consists of camera JPEG outputs.
